---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import Footer from "../components/Footer.astro";
import StickyMenu from "../components/StickyMenu.astro";
import ProjectPage from "../components/ProjectPage.astro";
---

<Layout>
	<StickyMenu />
	<ProjectPage title="drown: a 3d godot game" images={[]}>
		<p>
			This is a work in progress third person survival game built in Godot 4. My
			focus has been on core systems: dialogue that branches, basic AI, items
			and inventory logic, random loot. The visual side is rough for now. The
			animations are placeholders. The level is mostly just a greyboxed test
			space.
		</p>
		<p>
			I have learned a lot while building this, from architecture to shader
			work, and plenty of trial and error. Still, the project has been
			rewarding. The video below shows the current state of the game better than
			a long explanation would.
		</p>
		<div class="spacer"></div>
		<p style="padding-bottom: 1rem;">
			The mechanics demo below is thin on polish because the animation setup is
			not ready. Most of my time has gone into systems that do not show well on
			video. The project has several thousand lines of code but the repository
			is private. <br /><br /> My GitHub houses a few related projects. For the branching
			dialogue system I built a helper tool with Svelte Flow and Vite (see it on
			GitHub: <a
				href="https://github.com/emil-ke/Ramosa"
				class="accentLink"
				target="_blank">GitHub/emil-ke/Ramosa</a
			>). I also wrote a Godot scene switcher with fuzzy matching inspired by
			fzf and Telescope.nvim (demo on the GitHub page: <a
				href="https://github.com/emil-ke/slippery-scenes-godot"
				class="accentLink"
				target="_blank">GitHub/emil-ke/slippery-scenes-godot</a
			>). And I made a small plugin that mirrors vim's :b# command but for Godot
			scenes instead of buffers (<a
				href="https://github.com/emil-ke/go-to-last-scene.godot"
				class="accentLink"
				target="_blank">GitHub/emil-ke/go-to-last-scene.godot</a
			>).
		</p>
		<iframe
			width="100%"
			height="400"
			src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/KCvx3G9BA2o?si=9x-yhOmAfLaKddCf"
			title="Drown Demo"
			allow="accelerometer;
			autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture;
			web-share"
			referrerpolicy="strict-origin-when-cross-origin"
			allowfullscreen></iframe>
	</ProjectPage>
	<Footer />
</Layout>
